": "obj", "type": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "slickconf.builder.auto_config_call_handler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fn_or_cls", "type": {"name": "callable", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "slickconf.builder._wrap_ast_for_fn_with_closure_vars", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "module", "type": {"name": "ast.Module", "xref": {"fqname": "ast.Module", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "fn", "type": {"name": "types.FunctionType", "xref": {"fqname": "types.FunctionType", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "ast.Module", "xref": {"fqname": "ast.Module", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Wraps `module.body` in a function that defines closure variables for `fn`.\n\nIf `fn` has any free variables (i.e., it's `__code__.co_freevars` is not\nempty), we want to make sure that compiling its AST (assumed to be in the body\nof `module`) will create the same set of free variables in the resulting code\nobject. However, by default this won't happen, since we would be compiling\n`fn`'s AST in the absence of its original context (e.g., just compiling a\nnested function, and not the containing one).\n\nTo work around this issue, this function wraps `module.body` in another\n`FunctionDef` that defines dummy variables corresponding to `fn`'s free\nvariables. This causes the subsequent compile step to create the right set of\nfree variables, and allows us to use `fn.__closure__` when creating a\nnew function object via `types.FunctionType`.\n\nWe also add <_CALL_HANDLER_ID> as a final dummy variable, and append its value\n(the call handler) to `fn.__closure__` when creating the new function object.\n\nEffectively, this wrapping looks like the following Python code:\n\n    def __auto_config_closure_wrapper__():\n      closure_var_1 = None\n      closure_var_2 = None\n      ...\n      <_CALL_HANDLER_ID> = None\n\n      def fn(...):  # Or some expression involving a lambda.\n        ...  # Contains references to the closure variables.\n\nArgs:\n  module: An `ast.Module` object whose body contains the function definition\n    for `fn` (e.g., as an `ast.FunctionDef` or `ast.Lambda`).\n  fn: The function to create dummy closure variables for (assumed to\n    correspond to the body of `module`).\n\nReturns:\n  A new `ast.Module` containing an additional wrapper `ast.FunctionDef` that\n  defines dummy closure variables."]}, {"name": "slickconf.builder._find_function_code", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "code", "type": {"name": "types.CodeType", "xref": {"fqname": "types.CodeType", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "fn_name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Finds the code object within `code` corresponding to `fn_name`."]}, {"name": "slickconf.builder._unwrap_code_for_fn", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "code", "type": {"name": "types.CodeType", "xref": {"fqname": "types.CodeType", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "fn", "type": {"name": "types.FunctionType", "xref": {"fqname": "types.FunctionType", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Unwraps `code` to find the code object for `fn`.\n\nThis function assumes `code` is the result of compiling an `ast.Module`\nreturned by `_wrap_node_for_fn_with_closure_vars`.\n\nArgs:\n  code: A code object containing code for `fn`.\n  fn: The function to find a code object for within `code`.\n\nReturns:\n  The code object corresponding to `fn`."]}, {"name": "slickconf.builder._make_closure_cell", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "contents", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns `types.CellType(contents)`."]}, {"name": "slickconf.builder.config_fn", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fn", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "slickconf.builder.auto_config_from_source", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "source", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "slickconf.builder.finalize", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "node", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "slickconf.builder.build", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "__key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "__name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "slickconf.builder.build_init", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "__name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "slickconf.builder.build_fn", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "__name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "slickconf.builder.placehold